- Details of the pictures include all relevant information associated with a digital asset;
- Downloaded pictures are those that have a log entry with 'download' as the access type.

- 'Visuals' can refer to digital assets such as pictures or images;
- 'Creators' are the individuals who created the digital assets, represented by `user_name`;
- 'Writers' are those who wrote the articles, identified by `writer_name`.

- "voyagers" metaphorically refers to the users;
- "gazed upon" corresponds to the action of viewing;
- "visual treasure" is a metaphor for images;
- "vault of My Videos" refers to the "My Videos" collection.

sql:
SELECT asset_id, related_id, related_type, field, description
FROM digital_assets
WHERE related_type = 'writer';

SELECT DISTINCT w.writer_name
FROM writers w
JOIN articles a ON w.writer_id = a.writer_id;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT related_id) AS total_writers
FROM digital_assets
WHERE related_type = 'writer' AND related_id IS NOT NULL;

SELECT upload_file_id
FROM upload_files
WHERE file_name = 'image1.jpg';

SELECT file_type, SUM(file_size) AS total_size
FROM upload_files
GROUP BY file_type;

